## Skills — what's available and when to use each

### Your custom skills (in .claude/skills/)

prd-writer

- Trigger: any feature definition request

- Use: FIRST, before any planning or code

- Saves to: docs/prd-[feature-name].md

- Hands off to: /plan-eng-review or /autoplan

### GStack skills (use after your skills)

Planning chain (run in this order):

  /office-hours      → when scope is unclear, run BEFORE prd-writer

  /plan-ceo-review   → strategic check on any feature

  /plan-eng-review   → architecture review, reads the PRD file

  /autoplan          → generates task list, reads PRD + eng review

Build chain (run in this order):

  build              → Claude Code implements the approved plan

  /review            → code review against PRD acceptance criteria

  /cso               → security audit (auth, payments, user data only)

  /qa                → browser QA, uses PRD acceptance criteria

  /ship              → pre-ship checklist, opens PR

Utility (run when needed):

  /investigate       → root cause before any bug fix

  /careful           → activate before touching prod or risky files

  /retro             → every Friday, tracks shipping health

  /document-release  → after major features ship

## Standard chains

New feature:

  prd-writer → /plan-eng-review → /autoplan → build → /review → /qa → /ship

New feature (scope unclear):

  /office-hours → prd-writer → /plan-eng-review → /autoplan → build → /review → /qa → /ship

Security-sensitive feature:

  prd-writer → /plan-eng-review → /autoplan → build → /cso → /review → /qa → /ship

Bug fix:

  /careful → /investigate → fix → /review → /ship

## File conventions

- PRDs:        docs/prd-[feature-name].md

- ADRs:        docs/adr-[decision-name].md  (when you add that skill)

- Retros:      docs/retro-[date].md

## Rules Claude must follow in this repo

1. Always read the relevant PRD file before reviewing or planning

2. Never start building without an approved plan from /autoplan

3. Always run /investigate before fixing any bug

4. Always run /careful before touching files in /infra or /migrations

5. New skills go in .claude/skills/[skill-name]/SKILL.md and get

   registered in this file under "Your custom skills"

## Core workflows

New project:
  "new project" → new-project skill → CLAUDE.md created and committed

New feature:
  prd-writer → /plan-eng-review → /autoplan → build → /review → /qa → /ship

Unclear scope:
  /office-hours → prd-writer → /plan-eng-review → /autoplan → build → /review → /qa → /ship

Security-sensitive:
  prd-writer → /plan-eng-review → /autoplan → build → /cso → /review → /qa → /ship

Bug fix:
  /careful → /investigate → fix → /review → /deploy-checklist
